From 878e7b11736e062514e58f3b445ff343e6705537 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Haoxiang Li <haoxiang_li2024@163.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Feb 2025 11:04:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] nfp: bpf: Add check for nfp_app_ctrl_msg_alloc()
Git-commit: 878e7b11736e062514e58f3b445ff343e6705537
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc4
References: CVE-2025-21848 bsc#1239479

Add check for the return value of nfp_app_ctrl_msg_alloc() in
nfp_bpf_cmsg_alloc() to prevent null pointer dereference.

Fixes: ff3d43f7568c ("nfp: bpf: implement helpers for FW map ops")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Haoxiang Li <haoxiang_li2024@163.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250218030409.2425798-1-haoxiang_li2024@163.com
Signed-off-by: Paolo Abeni <pabeni@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Vasant Karasulli <vkarasulli@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/netronome/nfp/bpf/cmsg.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/netronome/nfp/bpf/cmsg.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/netronome/nfp/bpf/cmsg.c
index 2ec62c8d86e1..59486fe2ad18 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/netronome/nfp/bpf/cmsg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/netronome/nfp/bpf/cmsg.c
@@ -20,6 +20,8 @@ nfp_bpf_cmsg_alloc(struct nfp_app_bpf *bpf, unsigned int size)
 	struct sk_buff *skb;
 
 	skb = nfp_app_ctrl_msg_alloc(bpf->app, size, GFP_KERNEL);
+	if (!skb)
+		return NULL;
 	skb_put(skb, size);
 
 	return skb;
